Support Vector Machine

Jan 10, 2018

33

Make and plot some training data.

library(tidyverse)
## ── Attaching packages ────────────────────────────────────────────── tidyverse 1.2.1 ──
## ✔ ggplot2 2.2.1.9000     ✔ purrr   0.2.4     
## ✔ tibble  1.3.4          ✔ dplyr   0.7.4.9000
## ✔ tidyr   0.7.2          ✔ stringr 1.2.0     
## ✔ readr   1.1.1          ✔ forcats 0.2.0
## ── Conflicts ───────────────────────────────────────────────── tidyverse_conflicts() ──
## ✖ dplyr::filter() masks stats::filter()
## ✖ dplyr::lag()    masks stats::lag()
n = 10000
dat <- 
  tibble(
    a = runif(n),
    b = runif(n)
  )

dat1 <- 
  dat %>% 
    mutate(
      c = as.factor(sin(10*a) > b)
    )

ggplot(dat1, aes(x = a, y = b, colour = c)) +
  geom_point()

Model the data.

library(e1071)

model <- svm(c ~ ., data = dat1)
model
## 
## Call:
## svm(formula = c ~ ., data = dat1)
## 
## 
## Parameters:
##    SVM-Type:  C-classification 
##  SVM-Kernel:  radial 
##        cost:  1 
##       gamma:  0.5 
## 
## Number of Support Vectors:  2554

Predict new points and plot the surface.

dat_new <- 
  tibble(
    a = runif(1e04),
    b = runif(1e04)
  )

dat_new$c = predict(model, dat_new)

ggplot(dat_new, aes(x = a, y = b, colour = c)) +
  geom_point()
